<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">Prayer for Lent 2</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Mar 03, 2015 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
I see a man <br></br>
sleeping on a bench <br></br>
in the cold,
</p>

 <p>
And I say,
</p>

 <p>
“Thank you, Lord, <br></br>
for I am not like him.”
</p>

 <p>
I see a woman <br></br>
alone, in tears, <br></br>
mourning,
</p>

 <p>
And I say,
</p>

 <p>
“Thank you, Lord, <br></br>
for I am not like her.”
</p>

 <p>
I see a man <br></br>
upon a cross, <br></br>
humiliated, scorned, <br></br>
despised,
</p>

 <p>
And suddenly my <br></br>
foolish pride is clear <br></br>
even to me,
</p>

 <p>
And I cry,
</p>

 <p>
“Forgive me, Lord, <br></br>
for I am not like you.”
</p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>


